<br>
Also, I don't know many high level people, well, I know 3 off the top of my head, which is sad, but anyway.. if anyone would want to come along on a raid of these places let me know.. I'm dying (literally..) to finish my epic, but without a guild arranging battles and groups and such is near impossible. Thanks for your time.<br>
<br>
53rd Halfling Wanderer of Ayonae Ro -- ignore the sig, need to fix it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/unydiaywalmoriel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nydia Ywalmoriel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/7/02 8:09:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=422.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid Epic Mobs?</span><hr size=1> I can't speak for the big boys, such as Faydedear or VS, but *many* parts of the druid epic are doable with a single, even a single extremely offense light, group.  We killed the Corrupted Seahorse in Kedge recently with a single group, of 2 clerics, a chanter, a mage, his pet, and a monk, all levels 50-54, and we were ~50% mana when our puller brought it.  Unlike the swirlspines, which are very MR, the tainted/corrupted seahorse can be stunned just fine with cleric/chanter stuns, and even hit by magic based nukes.  He does hit very hard though, and be careful about your proximity when the Tainted is about to die, because the Corrupted will be very agro when he spawns.  I found this out the hard way when I fired off a stun just as the tainted died and then backed off, thinking I had missed the Corrupted; I was the sole fatality in that fight... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Best of luck in your epic quest!  Just because you are not guilded, does not mean that your epic is undoable; you can do many parts of it solo or with a single party.  You will, however, certainly need guild *help*, or the help of lots of friends, to finish it, and this means spending enough time grouping with people to build up a relationship with them such that they are going to find it worth their trouble to help you out on encounters the size of VS or Faydedear.  This means that you should expect to go on a *lot* of raids to help out others with their epics, etc; getting a guild/group to help do the larger portions of an epic is considered to be something you have to 'pay your dues' for.  While these mobs *can* be done as 'mercernary raids', the major guilds, by dint of their level of organization, tend to get to these spawns much quicker than you can cobble a free-lance group together, unless you have everyone committed ahead of time.  At level 53 there is no reason you should not be hitting zones which at least give you the opportunity to hook up with folks of like and higher level and begin networking, as it were; I began hitting KC (ugh) at 48, and Velks at 50, and folks up to 60 can frequently be found here, although arguably not all of them are the best candidates to help you out with your epic <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Btw, there is currently a 'tactics' thread discussing Faydedear in the 'raids' section of this board; you might want to check it out, if you are curious as to what is involved.<br>
<br>
